Comment: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:24.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.41,0:20:33.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable Romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.94,0:20:37.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:41.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.12,0:20:44.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.25,0:20:55.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:20:59.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.43,0:21:02.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.97,0:21:06.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.81,0:21:09.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.39,0:21:12.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:17.49,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.49,0:21:21.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.19,0:21:26.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.84,0:21:30.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.25,0:21:33.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.88,0:21:36.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.70,0:21:41.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.47,0:21:44.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:48.47,0:21:48.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,After suddenly finding a friend in each other, \NLuise and Lotte
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.62,0:00:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,changed they hairstyles to matching, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.77,0:00:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,surprising everyone around them \Nwith how indistinguishably alike the two girls can become.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.07,0:00:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,While just casually exchanging stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.29,0:00:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,an unthinkable revelation dawned upon them -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.86,0:00:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise and Lotte
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.39,0:00:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,are actually blood-related twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.31,0:00:28.51,Sign,,0,0,110,,{\c&HE1E8EE&\bord0\blur0.8\3c&H303339&}Episode 3 \N {\fs50} Oath by the Lake {湖の誓い}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.36,0:00:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, they are off \Nto somewhere else again, Luise and Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Since yesterday, those have been inseparable - \Nthick as thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.50,0:00:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And whenever they glance at one another,\Nthey grin like that - ear-to-ear!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.75,0:00:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a girl looking just like you around \Nis a mighty exhilarating thing, I imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.49,0:00:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, even after the lights went out, \NI heard them gossiping to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.68,0:01:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Think they might be scheming something again? \NThose two are a prankish bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They no longer even come out to play with us. \NThis must be a major conspiracy. {/there's some secret}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.17,0:01:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But they could at least tell me something!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.77,0:01:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, we somehow ended up \Nsurrendering Luise to Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.24,0:01:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.16,0:01:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, peculiar, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.67,0:01:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really so?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.70,0:01:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.34,0:01:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what I've been telling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.66,0:01:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad sure seems like an interesting guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.77,0:01:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, all the people coming to listen to the opera \Ndon't seem to share this view.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.60,0:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, as soon as he starts conducting the orchestra, \Nhe becomes so gravely serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.57,0:01:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Wish I could see it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.06,0:01:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But to me, he'll be sure to send a certain signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.38,0:01:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.66,0:01:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When the music is over and the audience is applauding, {/when they finish playing and receive the applause}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.64,0:01:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,while bowing, he sends a quick glance my way \Nand combs up his hair here with his left hand. {to push up (one's hair) with one's fingers; to comb up; to smooth back (a wisp of hair)}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.73,0:01:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.02,0:01:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I also applaud him with all my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.90,0:01:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.17,0:01:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, is mom actually a lot of a crybaby?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.90,0:01:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She never lets herself cry while someone is looking. {/before other people}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.57,0:02:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But to me, she always says this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.05,0:02:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"A woman shouldn't waste her tears on trifles. {lit: woman shouldn't shed cheap-looking; tawdry; insignificant tears - hope she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.72,0:02:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unforgivable for a woman \Nto break into tears to extort others' sympathy." {/if a woman cries because she wants to be treated with pity}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.35,0:02:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you didn't cry back then, \Neven after receiving my kick on the shins.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.49,0:02:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.75,0:02:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I so want to meet her, my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.47,0:02:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too! If only I could meet my dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.64,0:02:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, I'm writing a letter home today. \NI'm going to ask dad to send over a photo of himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.70,0:02:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,True? Sublime! My heart is pounding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.38,0:02:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, which one of us you think is older?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.05,0:02:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's hard to say. {/I don't know}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.91,0:02:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I had to guess, I'd say it was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.06,0:02:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, I have both a mom and a sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.41,0:02:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I so want to shout it for everyone to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't, we settled on it last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.45,0:02:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, we shouldn't tell anyone \Nwe're actual twin sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.63,0:02:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, it is so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.63,0:02:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know the full picture ourselves. {hope she means this by "full of things don't understand"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.67,0:03:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How come dad and mom no longer live together?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,First, of course, they got married.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.05,0:03:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they had us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.72,0:03:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they must have quarreled and parted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.51,0:03:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And they separated us just the same \Nas they separated mom's first name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But why didn't they ever ask us about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.13,0:03:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, whether or not we two\Nwish to be separated, too. {/split in two}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.16,0:03:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn't! By then, we were still little tots, \Nprobably hadn't even learned to talk yet. {/it's impossible - by then, we were toddlers/babies, unable to talk}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.29,0:03:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise! What are you doing in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you're scheming this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.07,0:03:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No scheming involved to my knowledge. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You only ever play with Lotte these days, \Nand brush us off as some gnat! It stings a bit. {/treating us as some bugs, isn't that rude}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't try to brush you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.39,0:03:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that me and Lotte \Nhave crucial matters to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.97,0:03:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Those could those be? {\i1}Crucial matters?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.05,0:03:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be a secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure. Keep sticking to each other \Nlike two cherries on a twig. {kusari is chain/leash, I think she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.32,0:03:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like anyone here wants to play anyway! {unsure, maybe she means "we won't be playing with you anymore" or "now we detest games"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what do you think could be that secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.27,0:04:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.70,0:04:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No you won't! Stephie! {no clue what is yoshinai}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.27,0:04:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what is that secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.18,0:04:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't say! It's something nobody \Nbut me and Lotte would understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.23,0:04:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't you tease me! {/don't tell me ill-natured; mean; nasty; sadistic; cruel; mean-spirited things}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.01,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In exchange, you can count on my help \Nnext time you two plan to prank everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.51,0:04:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, spill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're getting pesky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.09,0:04:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There are still more things we need to discuss \Nthan you can shake a stick at, and no time is enough for that! {https://thesaurus.weblio.jp/content/%E6%99%82%E9%96%93%E3%81%8C%E3%81%84%E3%81%8F%E3%82%89%E3%81%82%E3%81%A3%E3%81%A6%E3%82%82%E8%B6%B3%E3%82%8A%E3%81%AA%E3%81%84}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.19,0:04:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit getting in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.96,0:04:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise! You can't be shooing others away like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.91,0:04:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.28,0:04:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.94,0:04:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't take too close to heart what Luise said. {/Luise didn't say it out of malice either}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's true that for some while \Nwe won't be able to confide it in anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.03,0:04:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.65,0:04:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.48,0:04:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my. Now Luise even brought Stephie to tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for yourself, I'm not crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.21,0:04:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I no longer want to play \Nwith someone like Luise! {no clue what's first word, iindakara?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, those two sure are being strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.24,0:05:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Frau Braids and Frau Curls are back again? \NYou are no longer the one. {lit is "you're together again" but idk what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, \NI'm told you've taken a photo together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.64,0:05:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so? {lit is "when will it be ready" but it doesn't work with following "yes" in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.72,0:05:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We'll collect them the day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you'll send them home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll sure be a bolt from the blue \Nto both your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.12,0:05:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, meeting a friend who is a spitting image of you \Ncompletely by chance - it's not something you do every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When your parents's response arrives, \Nplease let me know it, too. See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, the picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.77,0:05:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No way we can send it home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! If they know we've met each other, \Nour play is blown! {/it will no longer be a secret\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care on your way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.58,0:06:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herr Eipeldauer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.80,0:06:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome. Come again, \Nwhenever you need a picture taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.44,0:06:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fine picture, if I do say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.72,0:06:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks just like something \Nthe illustrated magazines are looking for! {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E3%82%B0%E3%83%A9%E3%83%95%E8%AA%8C - no clue what to make of it in english, but it seems I'll have to drop "graph" part; illustrated magazine also just implies a gazette that has pictures in it, in addition to articles, and graphuzashi it seems is just something consisting entirely of pretty pictures, like an album}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.75,0:06:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If I send this picture home, \NI bet, dad jumps out of his skin, if not more. {probably otosan-tachi implies dad and the other people living with them here, but we only know of resi so far so no reason to overcomplicate it}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.02,0:06:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if dad recognizes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.31,0:06:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And what would mom have to say about this? \NAren't you curious? {/don't you wanna know}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.77,0:06:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't! \NThis picture must be kept for private eyes only.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.41,0:06:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, you really can't tell us apart here, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.13,0:07:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, the post had arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.29,0:07:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, a moment of silence, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.92,0:07:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to read the names now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.91,0:07:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first would be... Truda! \NNext is... Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.35,0:07:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Monica, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.29,0:07:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}our{\i0} dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.92,0:07:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go:{/I'll read}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.66,0:07:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"To my dearest, only child."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.40,0:07:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.39,0:07:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows perfectly well he has twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.38,0:08:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"I think you must have completely forgotten \Nwhat your old father looks like. {it's actually "head of the family" but I don't think it matters}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.31,0:08:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise you wouldn't be so anxious for a photo \Njust before the end of your vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I thought I would send you \Nmy usual photo of choice - {/my most favorite}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.95,0:08:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that pictures me as a baby, \Nsleeping in my birthday suit on a polar-bear skin. {/white bear fur}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.03,0:08:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But you wrote that it must be \Nan absolutely brand-new picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I rushed off to the photographer's, \Nand explained to him just why I needed it in such a hurry. {/took it with a super-express}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.80,0:08:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him that unless he took my picture, my Luise \Nwouldn't recognize me when I went to the station to meet her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm not as handsome as usual there \Nis because we did it in a hurry."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.34,0:08:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It really shows! {really unsure what she means here, usually I'd go "What do you think?" but here it clearly can't be the case so going with a guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.10,0:08:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm sorry for the counselors there. \NI hope you don't lead them such a dance as you do your father. {this is from the book, fumitsukeru is "to trample down; to tread on" and I'm not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.09,0:08:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I send you a thousand kisses \Nand am longing to have you home again." {/looking forward to the day I see you again in good health}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.72,0:08:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He sounds lovely! And funny, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.06,0:08:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, in the picture he looks quite serious. {to be affected; to put on airs}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.32,0:08:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He keeps a straight face in front of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.40,0:08:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we're alone we always have lots of fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.98,0:09:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, you mind if I keep it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.92,0:09:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.12,0:09:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you'll let me keep mom's photo, too, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find Stephie anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you searched everywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I checked every corner of the house and the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.57,0:09:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No signs of her anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.37,0:09:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.53,0:09:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.98,0:09:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You girls! Eavesdropping again, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.86,0:09:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Frau Muthesius \Nneed to discuss a pressing matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.33,0:09:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, out you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.75,0:10:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait a minute. Had anyone among you girls \Nseen or talked to Stephie this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.40,0:10:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time I checked, she was reading a letter \Nin the inner garden. {/back/rear part of the garden}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.03,0:10:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But soon after, she was no longer there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.52,0:10:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw her running towards the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.63,0:10:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To the lake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Muthesius!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't you be so alarmed. {calm down}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.88,0:10:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first course of action should be \Nsearching the area together. {/first, let's ask everyone to ... }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.03,0:10:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.64,0:10:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.88,0:10:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Please answer if you hear us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.81,0:10:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.97,0:10:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.69,0:10:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Stephie!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where could she have run off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.92,0:10:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Truda!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:10:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Any luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.78,0:10:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, it was your fault \Nthat Stephie decided to go missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.52,0:11:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that my fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.83,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how you upset Stephie today? {/offended/hurt}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.84,0:11:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.87,0:11:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't do anything of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You told her to get lost, didn't you? {/before, you told her to stop getting in the way}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.60,0:11:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie was extremely stung by that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.04,0:11:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But I... never...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.76,0:11:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this is happening because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.91,0:11:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Truda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get hung up on it, Luise. \NIt wasn't because of what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.59,0:11:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry up to find her instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.69,0:11:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie, where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.30,0:11:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer something, Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.32,0:11:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And there...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.21,0:12:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! She might just be over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.33,0:12:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,After me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.79,0:12:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.56,0:12:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,On this hill, there's a big tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.57,0:12:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you climb up there, a great view \Non the lake and on the summer camp opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.85,0:12:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.81,0:12:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise! Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.39,0:12:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing there? \NClimb down, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is sick worried about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.20,0:12:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can no longer climb down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.36,0:12:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what a strange thing to do. {/can't be helped/I've no choice}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.95,0:13:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.11,0:13:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.34,0:13:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You even managed to climb all the way here! {not bad at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.35,0:13:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,While climbing, I was in a daze. {forgetting oneself; daze; trance; ecstasy; delirium}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.66,0:13:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to just leave for somewhere else. {/go to another place, anywhere}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.56,0:13:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.15,0:13:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie, did I hurt you that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what in the world...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter arrived... from my mama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.36,0:13:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My papa and mama are breaking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.59,0:13:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The hearings started already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:14:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There, they're going to decide\Nwith which one of them I'm going to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.43,0:14:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They send you away on the vacations here \Nto do such a thing behind your back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.54,0:14:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mama is trying to find an ally in me. {lit: mama wants to become my ally - not sure, maybe it would rather be "mama wants me to stay with her"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And papa seems to have fallen in love \Nwith another woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.02,0:14:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already decided, I don't even get any say in it. {/can't be helped. whatever I say}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.38,0:14:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's worse, I feel that I am currently \Nthe most hapless girl in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.95,0:14:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm also hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.39,0:14:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's return, Stephie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephie! Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The counselors were scared to death! \NThey had already sent us to get a policeman! {to turn pale; to blanch (with fear)} {/they told us to let the police know/they went to involve the police}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's show you to the counselors already! {/hurry up to the staff room}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.62,0:14:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really have to do all this? {/really, where did you go}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.26,0:14:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.07,0:15:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dad hasn't got \Nanother woman{ that he loves} in the house, has he? {this pains me but this whole convo is hard to unravel, here they say "there's no another woman he loves" but two lines later they repeat it in a completely opposite sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.45,0:15:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.86,0:15:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If that had been true, \NI'd be the first person to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.13,0:15:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, could it be, that even if they're not married yet \Nthere's someone else he is in love with?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.94,0:15:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to my knowledge. {/I think not}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.34,0:15:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I daresay, I know nearly all of his friends. {unsure, maybe "but he has a lot of acquaintances and friends"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.66,0:15:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.12,0:15:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Does she have anyone? \NLike a... A man friend?"{/close/intimate man friend}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.15,0:15:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.22,0:15:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom keeps telling me this all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.16,0:15:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have my daughter Lotte, and I have my work, \Nand that's all I will ever ask of life." {/I don't need anything more from life}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.36,0:15:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My, but why, when, did dad and mom \Nbreak up in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.57,0:15:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if to split us, they went to court, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.93,0:15:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just two babies who don't yet understand a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.37,0:15:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,why did they have to keep us apart, \Nlike just some toy they couldn't share? {/separate/send to different places/keep us apart} {lit: the same as separating toys - I hope she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.33,0:16:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just that, they never told any of us \Nthat we have both another parent and a sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.74,0:16:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.92,0:16:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If not for the fluke that brought us together here, {/unless we would have met here by chance}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd be still going on with our lives, \Nwithout ever realizing we have a sibling this adorable! {/till the end of our days}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.97,0:16:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine parents we've got, haven't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.94,0:16:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait till we tell dad and mom a few things upfront! \NThat'll be sure to make them sit up! {lit: I will, one day, in front of dad and mom, tell them my complaints with all my might}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.30,0:16:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn't do such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.26,0:16:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.90,0:16:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we're still just children. {We couldn't do that," said Lottie timidly. "We're only children.} {lit: because we are too much children}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.26,0:17:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.96,0:17:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to talk, let's come out for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.87,0:17:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, where are you leading me to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.56,0:17:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.04,0:17:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At this hour? I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry, the moon is bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, when I first met you here, completely by accident, \Nit seemed like a thing straight out of a fairy tail. {/miracle}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.21,0:17:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it was due to the providence \Nwanting us two to meet. {/I can only think it was because god wanted us to meet}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.69,0:17:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you suggesting we pretend nothing of this ever happened, \Nreturn to our homes, and lead the same lives we led before? {lit: make a face like nothing happened, ... and keep on living like before this}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:17:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I'll be able to live on \Nwithout seeing you. {/it disgusts me to to not being able to see you}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.19,0:17:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do I. \NSo, I came up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be returning to Munich, \Nbut you'll come to Vienna with me instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.80,0:18:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To Vienna?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.96,0:18:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get to meet dad yourself! {/you wanna meet ... don't you}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.72,0:18:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to meet him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.42,0:18:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll confront dad together. {/meet/see}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.97,0:18:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll ask him for a permission \Nto see each other every now and then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.39,0:18:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if dad gets mad \Nand forbids us to see each other ever again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.51,0:18:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...he would do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.78,0:18:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I still might see dad if I become you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.49,0:18:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I will become you and go to Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.19,0:18:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll become me to go to Munich!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.09,0:18:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sublime!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.63,0:18:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Your idea is by a mile brighter than mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.55,0:18:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's great, if we both switch places! {/become one another}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.59,0:18:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But... are you sure it'll work?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:18:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen yourself how alike we are. \NNo way it doesn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do it, Lotte! {/let's try}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.69,0:19:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get to meet my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.33,0:19:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll meet my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.06,0:19:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so excited to get to know him! {lit: i wanna know various things}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.85,0:19:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then... Then, if it would seem possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.80,0:19:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.03,0:19:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.98,0:19:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you mean. {/Ithink so too}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.21,0:19:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.71,0:19:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and mom do that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.63,0:19:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the promise is sealed. {/token/symbol/evidence/sign}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.84,0:19:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We swear an oath of guarding this secret. {word from ep title}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.17,0:19:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Before us, a task of unprecedented magnitude. {/we're about to do big/important/difficult thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.12,0:19:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting tomorrow, we'll put our minds \Nto developing the strategy. {lit: immegiately tomorrow-on we've no choice but to kakaru (unsure what it is here) strategy and preparations}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.39,0:19:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do our very best, {\i1}Lotte!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.99,0:19:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Only after you, {\i1}Luise!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.45,0:20:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What just started as but a vague idea, {lit: tiny plan; strategy began}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.83,0:20:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,unbeknownst to the two girls behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.31,0:20:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is yet to evolve into a daring adventure \Nthrough the uncharted seas. {lit: require something like an embarkation on a great adventure/grand trip/voyage through unknown/unmarked seas/waters}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.29,0:20:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Luise and Lotte \Nknow that this journey is not for the faint of heart. {unsure, maybe he means the completely opposite: they hearts tremble/dance in excitement for the adventure}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.19,0:20:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They set their sights on an untrodden new continent. {/they dream of discovering a new continent}
